Former District Six residents can't wait for Hanover Street's name to be restored on Heritage Day. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Hanover Street will be reinstated on Tuesday, 24 September. It was renamed Keizersgracht Street under the Group Areas Act during apartheid. READ: District Six residents want to reclaim a piece of history At the same time, District Six was changed to Zonnebloem and became a whites-only area. Former Hanover Street residents say the name will bring back fond memories and will be one step towards restoring some of the history of the area. A process is also underway to rename Zonnebloem and change it back to District Six.